function:
long	ft_atoi_base(char *s, short base);

description:
the purpose of this function is te translation of a string into a long value, by conversion 'base'.
In the main.c file there is the function call with preset base 16, and the input string is taken from argv[1]

examples ():
$>./test 100
256

$>./test f
15

$>./test ---15
-21